        "This market tracks the likely legal, political, and personal outcomes for Omoyele Sowore in his ongoing case with the Department of State Services (DSS).\r\n\r\nOn 16 September 2025, the DSS filed a five-count charge at the Federal High Court in Abuja (case FHC/ABJ/CR/484/2025), naming Omoyele Sowore, X (formerly Twitter), and Meta (Facebook) as defendants.\r\n\r\nSowore is accused of publishing posts (on 25 and 26 August 2025) labelling President Tinubu “a criminal” and accusing him of lying about corruption, which the prosecution says amounted to publishing false information, defamation, and incitement of public disorder under the Cybercrimes (Prohibition, Prevention, etc.) Amendment Act, 2024 and sections of the Criminal Code Act.",
