      description:
        "In the previous FY 2025 cycle, GTCO maintained its crown as the highest dividend payer per share in the banking sector by declaring a historic total of ₦12.76 per share. Zenith Bank, however, demonstrated massive aggressive momentum by doubling its payout from the previous year to hit a strong ₦10.00 total per share for 2025. \r\n\r\nThis market tracks the highly competitive race between Nigeria’s top two banking powerhouses, Guaranty Trust Holding Company Plc (GTCO) and Zenith Bank Plc, to see which institution will deliver the highest cumulative dividend payout per share for the Full Financial Year (FY) 2026.\r\n\r\nThis market will remain open through 2026 and will resolve only after both corporate entities have officially audited and published their FY 2026 final financial statements (expected around March/April 2027).\r\n\r\nResolution will be based on official  announcement filings and  Financial Statements published by both Zenith Bank Plc and GTCO on the Nigerian Exchange Group (NGX) issuer portal",
